This project is a React-to-Next.js migration for a sneaker e-commerce frontend.

Tech stack:
- Next.js (App Router)
- JavaScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion only when necessary

Rules:
- Preserve the existing UI structure, responsiveness, and overall UX behavior
- Modernize the UI to feel cleaner, premium, and production-ready without changing the core design identity
- Avoid Bootstrap-style crowded layouts and outdated spacing patterns
- Keep layouts visually consistent with the original project while improving polish and maintainability
- Do NOT heavily redesign components unless explicitly requested
- Do NOT modify unrelated files
- Do NOT overwrite or delete the old React implementation during migration
- Migrate incrementally component-by-component
- Use modular, reusable, scalable component architecture
- Use Tailwind CSS only for styling
- Avoid unnecessary complexity, overengineering, and excessive abstractions
- Preserve accessibility and responsive behavior
- Use clean production-style code organization
- Prefer reusable UI patterns and optimized rendering practices

When generating code:
- Analyze the existing implementation first
- Preserve functionality and UX behavior
- Keep JSX structure clean and minimal
- Keep responsiveness intact across all breakpoints
- Make the UI feel more modern and premium without changing the overall layout structure